No. Facts produce statistics.A statistic of approximately 45% of all married couples divorcing someday, would be based on already existing facts about divorce rates, not speculation. Stereotypes are based on opinions, random observations, and speculation.With statistics, there is control and reason, as well as numerical data.Stereotypes are just words.